      "weight_variable_name": null,
      "weight_fields_interpretation": "The study uses PISA 2022 Spanish student data and reports using the entire student sample (n = 30,800) with 74 variables, followed by preprocessing and dimensionality reduction. The manuscript does not report applying PISA sampling weights or any replicate-weight procedure (e.g., BRR/jackknife), nor does it name a weight variable (such as W_FSTUWT/TOTWGT). Because the analysis relies on k-means clustering and supervised classification pipelines with SHAP-based interpretability, the paper does not indicate any complex-survey-weight-aware estimation. Therefore, the weighting strategy is not documented and is treated as unweighted/weight-omitted for the ML components."
    },
    "plausible_values_handling": "rubin_rules",
    "missing_data_handling": "multiple_imputation",
    "handling_not_reported_explanation": null,
